      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Jan 17 article about plans to extend Today television program</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in The Arts last Wednesday about NBC's plans to extend the ''Today'' program to a fourth hour attributed an erroneous distinction to the show. ''Nightwatch'' on CBS, which had its premiere in 1982, ran for four hours on weekdays. ''Today'' will not be the first such weekday program of that length on major broadcast networks.</p>
      </block>
